------------------------------------------------------------------------
Compliance with Upstream README Requirements
------------------------------------------------------------------------

The upstream Telegram-iOS README requests the following from forks:

  1. Use your own api_id.
     → N/A. BeHappy uses its own protocol (MVSy 1.0), not MTProto.
        No Telegram api_id is used by this fork.

  2. Do not use the name "Telegram" for your app.
     → Complied. The app is named "BeHappy" throughout user-visible
        surfaces. The string "Telegram" appears only in source code
        comments and copyright headers as required by attribution.

  3. Do not use the Telegram logo.
     → Complied. BeHappy uses its own independent logo and brand
        identity. No Telegram visual assets are bundled in the
        product.

  4. Follow Telegram's security guidelines.
     → Adopted in good faith. Cryptographic primitives, key handling,
        and transport security inherit upstream best practices.

  5. Publish your code to comply with the licences.
     → Complied. This repository is public.

